# IMPLEMENTATION METADATA PLAN v2.0

## Objective
The goal is to replace the generic GitHub/Lovable previews with a professional, robust metadata suite tailored for **SecureGuard Systems**. This includes a custom-generated website snapshot and comprehensive social media integration (Open Graph, Twitter Cards).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Snapshot Taken!**
> I have already generated a fresh, high-quality snapshot of the website (1200x630px) and saved it to `public/og-image.png`. This snapshot captures the latest visual enhancements (glows, gradients) and is ready for use.

---

## đź›  Proposed Metadata Architecture

### 1. Core SEO & Identity
Clean up the `<head>` section to ensure search engines have the correct context.
- **Title**: `SecureGuard Systems | Professional Security & Smart Home Installation`
- **Description**: `Premier security system installation across Essex and Suffolk. Specializing in CCTV, Access Control, Intercoms, and Intruder Alarms for Residential, Commercial, and Retail properties.`
- **Canonical URL**: Ensure a canonical link is present to prevent duplicate content issues.
- **Theme Color**: Set a hex color (e.g., `#0A0A0A` for dark mode) to brand the browser UI on mobile.

### 2. Social Media (Open Graph - Facebook, LinkedIn, Discord)
Replace the `lovable.dev` placeholders with local assets and branding.
- `og:title`: `SecureGuard Systems - Professional Security You Can Rely On`
- `og:description`: `Request a free security assessment for your home or business in Essex and Suffolk.`
- `og:image`: Point to `/og-image.png` (the fresh snapshot).
- `og:url`: Define the production URL.
- `og:type`: `website`
- `og:site_name`: `SecureGuard Systems`

### 3. Twitter / X Cards
Ensure links shared on X look premium and high-impact.
- `twitter:card`: `summary_large_image` (to display the snapshot prominently).
- `twitter:title`: `SecureGuard Systems | Security Professionals`
- `twitter:description`: `Professional security system installation across Essex and Suffolk.`
- `twitter:image`: Point to `/og-image.png`.

